I'll get the other box.

250
00:19:41,718 --> 00:19:43,660
I hope he falls and breaks his neck.

251
00:19:43,734 --> 00:19:48,175
I'm sure he'll fall. But I don't think we're
lucky enough to have him break his neck.

252
00:19:50,518 --> 00:19:51,794
Let's go.

253
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:22,677
These gusty winds appear to be playing
havoc with the giant nutcracker float.

254
00:20:22,903 --> 00:20:26,700
At this point, I can't even see the nuts.
They must have blown away.

255
00:20:27,095 --> 00:20:31,187
But nothing is going to dampen the spirit
of this holiday crowd, I can tell you that.

256
00:20:31,256 --> 00:20:33,645
Oh, here they are. Here come the nuts.

257
00:21:47,581 --> 00:21:51,193
Would it be indecent
to ask the grandparents to stay at a hotel?

258
00:21:52,381 --> 00:21:55,064
Can we at least forbid them
to answer the phone?

259
00:21:55,132 --> 00:21:57,783
Alexander called this morning
and Grandpa Clark told him...

260
00:21:57,852 --> 00:22:00,952
...I couldn't come to the phone
'cause I was going to the bathroom.

261
00:22:01,022 --> 00:22:03,094
We're all making sacrifices, Audrey.

262
00:22:03,421 --> 00:22:04,283
Everybody?

263
00:22:04,350 --> 00:22:08,212
Do you sleep with your brother? Do you
know how sick and twisted that is?

264
00:22:08,286 --> 00:22:12,279
I'm sleeping with your father.
Don't be so dramatic.

265
00:22:12,829 --> 00:22:17,020
I have nightmares about what he does in
bed alone when I'm not lying next to him.

266
00:22:17,247 --> 00:22:20,443
I don't know what to say
except it's Christmas...

267
00:22:20,862 --> 00:22:22,618
...and we're all in misery.

268
00:22:23,486 --> 00:22:25,941
Ellen, are you smoking again?

269
00:22:26,814 --> 00:22:28,188
No!

270
00:22:38,975 --> 00:22:41,342
Dad, where do you want these reindeer?

271
00:22:41,631 --> 00:22:43,736
Just put them on the lawn, Russ.

272
00:22:45,888 --> 00:22:47,710
I can't find the Santa Claus.

273
00:22:48,928 --> 00:22:51,710
It's in the basement. We'll get it later.

274
00:23:45,411 --> 00:23:47,648
Clark? Dinner's ready.

275
00:23:48,611 --> 00:23:50,749
Okay, honey. I'm starving.

276
00:24:09,092 --> 00:24:13,282
Obviously something broke the window.
Something hit the stereo.

277
00:24:22,629 --> 00:24:25,181
And why is the carpet all wet, Todd?

278
00:24:25,317 --> 00:24:27,586
I don't know, Margo.

279
00:24:35,174 --> 00:24:38,207
You wanna hurry this up, Clark?
I'm freezing my baguettes off.

280
00:24:38,277 --> 00:24:42,401
Two hundred and fifty strands of lights,
100 individual bulbs per strand...

281
00:24:42,789 --> 00:24:46,238
...for a grand total of 25,000
imported Italian twinkle lights.

282
00:24:48,550 --> 00:24:49,663
Twenty-five thousand.

283
00:24:49,798 --> 00:24:51,903
I hope nobody I know drives by...

284
00:24:52,070 --> 00:24:55,550
...and sees me standing in the yard,
staring at my house in my pajamas.

285
00:24:55,622 --> 00:24:58,623
If they know your dad,
they won't think anything of it.

286
00:24:58,695 --> 00:25:00,124
Fire it up!

287
00:25:01,319 --> 00:25:05,345
I dedicate this house
to the Griswold family Christmas.

288
00:25:08,423 --> 00:25:09,732
Drum roll, please.

289
00:25:12,263 --> 00:25:13,246
Drum roll.

290
00:25:27,432 --> 00:25:30,946
"Joy to the world."

291
00:25:44,714 --> 00:25:46,088
Beautiful, Clark.

292
00:25:47,018 --> 00:25:49,090
Talk about pissing your money away.

293
00:25:49,898 --> 00:25:54,120
I hope you kids see what a silly waste
of resources this was.

294
00:25:54,377 --> 00:25:56,287
He worked really hard, Grandma.

295
00:25:56,522 --> 00:25:58,213
So do washing machines.

296
00:26:02,955 --> 00:26:04,777
Let's get in where it's warm.

297
00:26:05,418 --> 00:26:09,891
Clark, baby, I can picture it
in my mind and it's breathtaking.

298
00:26:13,227 --> 00:26:14,339
Thanks, Mom.

299
00:26:15,019 --> 00:26:19,841
It's probably a bad bulb. You know, if
one goes out, the whole thing won't work.

300
00:26:20,075 --> 00:26:23,109
If I were you,
I'd personally check each one.

301
00:26:23,339 --> 00:26:24,615
I did that, Dad.

302
00:26:24,843 --> 00:26:28,553
If you need any help, give me a holler.
I'll be upstairs asleep.

303
00:26:30,540 --> 00:26:34,697
I'm sorry, Daddy. It looks good,
even if they're not lit.

304
00:26:36,236 --> 00:26:37,763
Thank you, sweetheart.

305
00:26:43,981 --> 00:26:46,534
Well, Dad, it was a good try.

306
00:26:46,861 --> 00:26:48,138
Thanks, Russ.

307
00:26:50,701 --> 00:26:52,970
We checked every bulb, didn't we?

308
00:26:54,604 --> 00:26:56,709
I'm sure of it.

309
00:26:59,694 --> 00:27:01,603
Maybe we ought to go up there and just...

310
00:27:01,677 --> 00:27:03,335
Geez! Look at the time.

311
00:27:04,205 --> 00:27:05,634
I have to go to bed.

312
00:27:06,125 --> 00:27:07,947
Brush my teeth, feed the hog.

313
00:27:08,045 --> 00:27:12,105
I still got some homework to do,
do the laundry, wash the car...

314
00:27:17,839 --> 00:27:19,813
Don't stay up too late.

315
00:27:40,463 --> 00:27:42,733
Get off me, you little fungus.

316
00:29:38,966 --> 00:29:41,356
Where the hell is that cold coming from?

317
00:30:03,447 --> 00:30:06,317
- I need just a few more...
- Pay by check, if you can.

318
00:30:06,808 --> 00:30:09,677
- Not a card?
- No, it's a hassle if you have to return.

319
00:30:16,408 --> 00:30:17,204
Help!

320
00:30:17,273 --> 00:30:19,444
Daddy. Is Clark coming?

321
00:30:19,512 --> 00:30:20,722
How the hell would I know?

322
00:30:20,792 --> 00:30:21,720
Is he in the house?

323
00:30:21,784 --> 00:30:24,566
If he's not farting around
with the lights, he must be.

324
00:30:24,632 --> 00:30:27,383
I'm sure he wants to come shopping
and have lunch with us.

325
00:30:27,449 --> 00:30:32,151
He's got another car. He can drive.
I have to eat so I can take my back pill.

326
00:34:24,454 --> 00:34:27,105
I want to take off these clothes,
sit with a glass of wine...

327
00:34:27,174 --> 00:34:29,029
...and kiss every inch of your body.

328
00:34:29,094 --> 00:34:31,811
- After you shower, of course.
- Of course.

329
00:34:47,495 --> 00:34:49,829
- Sparky?
- Yes, honey.

330
00:34:58,504 --> 00:35:01,820
Are you out here for a reason,
or are you just avoiding the family?

331
00:35:02,152 --> 00:35:04,869
I still have a couple hundred
more bulbs to check.

332
00:35:05,767 --> 00:35:07,591
Meantime, I can light the Santa...

333
00:35:07,657 --> 00:35:10,788
...and the eight tiny reindeer
and the "Merry Christmas" sign.

334
00:35:10,856 --> 00:35:13,245
That should look good. Ready?

335
00:35:13,513 --> 00:35:15,105
Want me to do the drum roll thing?

336
00:35:15,176 --> 00:35:17,184
No, it's okay. Here goes nothing.

337
00:35:24,617 --> 00:35:26,178
I don't understand it.

338
00:35:27,817 --> 00:35:30,916
The house lights don't work,
the floodlights don't work.

339
00:35:33,097 --> 00:35:34,526
Is it plugged in?

340
00:35:34,857 --> 00:35:37,575
Do you think I would check
thousands of tiny lights...

341
00:35:37,642 --> 00:35:40,576
...if I wasn't sure
the extension cord was plugged in?

342
00:35:42,378 --> 00:35:44,767
You used more than one cord, didn't you?

343
00:35:47,018 --> 00:35:50,728
Maybe the kids have been fooling around
with it. I'll check in the back.

344
00:36:10,795 --> 00:36:11,723
Clark!

345
00:36:14,219 --> 00:36:15,877
- Todd!
- Sorry!

346
00:36:19,371 --> 00:36:21,673
Honey, I think I know what's wrong.

347
00:36:36,621 --> 00:36:37,734
I can't see!

348
00:36:55,662 --> 00:36:57,004
This ought to do it.

349
00:37:10,191 --> 00:37:11,140
I fixed it!

350
00:37:14,543 --> 00:37:17,260
Everybody! Come out quick!
Look at the lights!

351
00:37:25,936 --> 00:37:27,823
- Get a towel.
- Okay!

352
00:37:31,408 --> 00:37:33,099
Wait a minute! I don't believe this.

353
00:37:33,168 --> 00:37:35,372
What's all that yelling about?

354
00:37:37,104 --> 00:37:38,631
What's going on here?!

355
00:37:40,624 --> 00:37:42,380
Twenty-five thousand twinkle lights.

356
00:37:44,145 --> 00:37:45,574
What's he doing?

357
00:37:45,809 --> 00:37:47,369
I haven't the foggiest.

358
00:37:49,488 --> 00:37:51,016
What the hell?!

359
00:37:51,730 --> 00:37:53,704
What is wrong with this?!

360
00:37:55,345 --> 00:37:56,839
Damn it!

361
00:38:01,330 --> 00:38:02,671
You goddamn thing!

362
00:38:34,227 --> 00:38:35,722
Dad, it's beautiful!

363
00:38:51,029 --> 00:38:52,851
Oh, my carpet!

364
00:39:02,132 --> 00:39:03,987
Clark, it's so lovely.

365
00:39:07,189 --> 00:39:09,906
You deserve a home like this
to spend Christmas in.

366
00:39:12,949 --> 00:39:15,338
It's a beaut, Clark. A beaut.

367
00:39:17,430 --> 00:39:20,300
You taught me everything I know
about exterior illumination.

368
00:39:20,374 --> 00:39:22,065
Thank you, thank you.

369
00:39:23,254 --> 00:39:24,596
Russ. Audrey.

370
00:39:28,790 --> 00:39:31,027
Dear... Francis.

371
00:39:33,750 --> 00:39:36,468
I hope this adds
to your enjoyment of the holidays.

372
00:39:36,791 --> 00:39:38,700
It's just wonderful.

373
00:39:40,951 --> 00:39:42,063
Arthur.

374
00:39:43,031 --> 00:39:43,980
Art.

375
00:39:45,591 --> 00:39:46,703
Dad.

376
00:39:47,191 --> 00:39:48,685
Thanks for being here.

377
00:39:48,951 --> 00:39:51,286
The little lights are not twinkling.

378
00:39:51,352 --> 00:39:53,905
I know, Art, and thanks for noticing.

379
00:39:58,232 --> 00:40:00,621
The house sure does look swell, Clark.

380
00:40:00,695 --> 00:40:01,972
Thanks, Eddie.

381
00:40:02,392 --> 00:40:06,386
I hope it enhances your holiday spirit.
Dear Catherine.

382
00:40:06,712 --> 00:40:08,273
Eddie?

383
00:40:09,496 --> 00:40:11,885
The house is gorgeous, Clark.

384
00:40:12,953 --> 00:40:14,065
Eddie?

385
00:40:14,552 --> 00:40:17,422
I hope you didn't do this
all on our account, Clark.

386
00:40:17,753 --> 00:40:21,201
Kids, come on out here and see
what Uncle Clark's done to the house.

387
00:40:21,273 --> 00:40:22,288
Eddie?

388
00:40:29,434 --> 00:40:30,361
Eddie?

389
00:40:33,114 --> 00:40:35,984
If you don't remember, this here is Rocky.

390
00:40:37,178 --> 00:40:40,473
- Have you got a kiss for me?
- Take a rain check on that, Art.

391
00:40:40,538 --> 00:40:43,255
He's got a lip fungus
that ain't identified yet.

392
00:40:45,850 --> 00:40:47,760
You remember Ruby Sue?

393
00:40:50,075 --> 00:40:51,831
Oh, my gosh!

394
00:40:53,595 --> 00:40:55,318
Her eyes are not crossed anymore.

395
00:40:55,387 --> 00:40:56,794
That somethin', ain't it?

396
00:40:56,859 --> 00:40:58,866
She falls in a well, her eyes go cross.

397
00:40:58,939 --> 00:41:02,235
A mule kicks her, they go back to normal.
I don't know.

398
00:41:05,756 --> 00:41:07,829
And this here is our pride and joy.

399
00:41:07,900 --> 00:41:09,274
Snots.

400
00:41:10,140 --> 00:41:11,252
Pretty name.

401
00:41:11,356 --> 00:41:14,291
We named him that
'cause he's got this sinus condition.

402
00:41:15,036 --> 00:41:18,232
Snots, you roll over
and let Uncle Clark scratch your belly.

403
00:41:20,317 --> 00:41:23,514
You never seen a set on a dog
like this one's got, Clark.

404
00:41:24,316 --> 00:41:25,877
That's okay, Eddie.

405
00:41:26,236 --> 00:41:28,789
That's somethin', ain't it?
You pet him on the belly...

406
00:41:28,860 --> 00:41:30,965
...and he'll love you till the day you die.

407
00:41:31,036 --> 00:41:33,524
I really shouldn't.
My hands are all chapped.

408
00:41:34,077 --> 00:41:38,550
We were going to call,
but Eddie wanted to make it a surprise.

409
00:41:38,781 --> 00:41:40,058
You surprised?

410
00:41:40,318 --> 00:41:41,300
Surprised, Eddie?

411
00:41:41,597 --> 00:41:43,801
If I woke up tomorrow
with my head sewn to the carpet...

412
00:41:43,965 --> 00:41:46,299
...I wouldn't be more surprised
than I am right now.

413
00:41:48,477 --> 00:41:50,388
We have plenty of room.

414
00:41:52,478 --> 00:41:55,893
Plenty of towels. Plenty of everything.

415
00:41:57,438 --> 00:42:01,268
We're pretty well set up here in the RV.
It's a little tight but...

416
00:42:01,822 --> 00:42:03,284
...we didn't come to impose.

417
00:42:03,358 --> 00:42:05,115
There's plenty of room.

418
00:42:05,535 --> 00:42:07,510
Quit being so damn polite, Ed.

419
00:42:08,287 --> 00:42:13,338
Catherine and I are pretty comfy in there,
but maybe you folks wouldn't mind...

420
00:42:13,407 --> 00:42:15,033
...the youngsters shacking up with you.

421
00:42:15,103 --> 00:42:16,859
After that long drive...

422
00:42:16,959 --> 00:42:19,513
...we could use
a little private time together.

423
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:25,371
Honey, why don't you get the kids' things.
Don't forget the rubber sheets and gerbils.

424
00:42:25,440 --> 00:42:27,196
I'll show you the home.

425
00:43:03,747 --> 00:43:05,656
That's a honey of a tree, Clark.

426
00:43:06,562 --> 00:43:07,675
Is it real?

427
00:43:08,643 --> 00:43:10,333
I dug it out of the ground myself.

428
00:43:10,402 --> 00:43:11,679
Is that a fact?

429
00:43:12,162 --> 00:43:13,788
Get out of there, Snots!

430
00:43:13,858 --> 00:43:14,806
Don't worry about it.

431
00:43:14,882 --> 00:43:17,304
A little tree water ain't gonna hurt him.

432
00:43:17,443 --> 00:43:20,258
Before we left, he drank
a half a quart of Pennzoil.

433
00:43:20,324 --> 00:43:23,040
He lifted his leg the next mornin'...

434
00:43:25,315 --> 00:43:28,065
If he drinks the water out of there,
the tree's gonna dry up.

435
00:43:28,131 --> 00:43:29,757
Come on out of there.

436
00:43:31,043 --> 00:43:35,353
Get out of there. Go in the kitchen
and get something to eat.

437
00:43:36,068 --> 00:43:37,694
He's cute, ain't he?

438
00:43:37,764 --> 00:43:41,506
Only problem is, he's got
a little bit of Mississippi leg hound in him.

439
00:43:41,764 --> 00:43:45,822
If the mood catches him right,
he'll grab your leg and just go to town.

440
00:43:47,044 --> 00:43:50,722
You don't want him around
if you're wearing short pants.

441
00:43:51,845 --> 00:43:53,274
A word of warning, though.

442
00:43:53,349 --> 00:43:56,447
If he does lay into you,
it's best to just let him finish.

443
00:43:59,044 --> 00:44:02,492
I can't believe you're actually
standing here in my living room, Eddie.

444
00:44:02,758 --> 00:44:04,165
Never thought the day would come.

445
00:44:04,230 --> 00:44:05,986
I'm excited about it, too.

446
00:44:07,046 --> 00:44:09,763
It's a cryin' shame
the older kids couldn't make it.

447
00:44:13,349 --> 00:44:15,684
I'll get that.
Don't worry about it. It's okay.

448
00:44:19,814 --> 00:44:23,840
I got the daughter in the clinic
getting cured off the Wild Turkey.

449
00:44:24,743 --> 00:44:28,387
The older boy, bless his soul,
is preparing for his career.

450
00:44:28,966 --> 00:44:30,460
- College?
- Carnival.

451
00:44:31,526 --> 00:44:32,737
You gotta be proud.

452
00:44:34,248 --> 00:44:38,274
Last season, he was a pixie dust spreader
on the Tilt-O-Whirl.

453
00:44:38,567 --> 00:44:41,601
He thinks that maybe next year,
he'll be guessing people's weight...

454
00:44:41,671 --> 00:44:43,646
...or barking for the Yak Woman.

455
00:44:45,127 --> 00:44:46,982
- You ever see her?
- No.

456
00:44:47,047 --> 00:44:50,244
She got these big horns
growing right out above her ears.

457
00:44:50,472 --> 00:44:52,860
She's ugly as sin, but a sweet gal.

458
00:44:52,936 --> 00:44:54,081
And a hell of a good cook.

459
00:44:54,152 --> 00:44:56,738
Can I refill your eggnog for you?
Get you something to eat?

460
00:44:56,808 --> 00:44:59,197
Drive you out to the middle of nowhere
and leave you for dead?

461
00:44:59,272 --> 00:45:01,344
No, I'm doing just fine.

462
00:45:01,896 --> 00:45:03,206
Just glad to be here.

463
00:45:04,809 --> 00:45:07,362
When did you get
the tenement on wheels?

464
00:45:08,169 --> 00:45:10,885
Oh, that? That's an RV.

465
00:45:12,296 --> 00:45:13,922
I borrowed it off a buddy of mine.

466
00:45:13,993 --> 00:45:16,710
He took my house, I took the RV.

467
00:45:17,609 --> 00:45:19,519
It's a good-looking vehicle, ain't it?

468
00:45:20,170 --> 00:45:22,025
It looks so nice parked in the driveway.

469
00:45:22,090 --> 00:45:25,286
It sure does.
Don't you go falling in love with it.

470
00:45:25,993 --> 00:45:28,960
We're taking it with us
when we leave here next month.

471
00:45:38,411 --> 00:45:41,128
Get Ed Leftic up here
to look over these figures!

472
00:45:41,674 --> 00:45:43,747
Retooling. That's a great excuse.

473
00:45:45,770 --> 00:45:48,008
Retooling?! I'll retool you!

474
00:45:50,891 --> 00:45:52,801
Mr. Shirley, Merry Christmas.

475
00:45:53,195 --> 00:45:54,405
Who's that?

476
00:45:55,307 --> 00:45:56,900
It's me, Clark Griswold.

477
00:45:57,131 --> 00:45:58,473
What do you want?

478
00:45:59,531 --> 00:46:03,689
My wife and I just came up with
a little something special. It's a gift.

479
00:46:04,716 --> 00:46:07,204
Put it over there
with the others, Greaseball.

480
00:46:17,453 --> 00:46:21,730
By the way, I hope my report helped out
at the trade show.

481
00:46:26,413 --> 00:46:28,322
I'm sure it did, Grisball.

482
00:46:29,037 --> 00:46:32,234
If you'll excuse me,
I'm in the middle of an important call.

483
00:46:33,134 --> 00:46:34,443
Get me somebody.

484
00:46:34,573 --> 00:46:35,751
Anybody.

485
00:46:37,389 --> 00:46:38,982
And get me somebody while I'm waiting.

486
00:46:51,438 --> 00:46:55,431
This is a new non-caloric,
silicon-based kitchen lubricant...

487
00:46:55,534 --> 00:46:56,810
...my company's been working on.

488
00:46:56,879 --> 00:47:00,424
It creates a surface 500 times
more slippery than cooking oil.

489
00:47:00,494 --> 00:47:02,829
We'll fly down the hill with this stuff.

490
00:47:03,215 --> 00:47:05,190
Has anyone ever used it on a sled?

491
00:47:05,263 --> 00:47:06,670
Not that I know of.

492
00:47:09,135 --> 00:47:12,004
Don't go puttin' none of that stuff
on my sled, Clark.

493
00:47:12,335 --> 00:47:15,532
- You know the metal plate in my head?
- How could I forget it.

494
00:47:15,695 --> 00:47:19,373
I had it replaced. Every time
Catherine raved up the microwave...

495
00:47:19,504 --> 00:47:22,221
