01:09:41,689 --> 01:09:42,965
Merry Christmas.

747
01:09:46,745 --> 01:09:48,436
- I can't believe it.
- What is it?

748
01:09:49,082 --> 01:09:51,799
A letter confirming your reservation
at the nuthouse?

749
01:09:52,410 --> 01:09:53,555
It's from my company.

750
01:09:54,330 --> 01:09:55,093
Your bonus.

751
01:09:55,802 --> 01:09:56,663
My bonus.

752
01:10:02,201 --> 01:10:03,926
Open it, Clarkie. Open it.

753
01:10:04,571 --> 01:10:06,643
I hope it's a fortune.

754
01:10:07,291 --> 01:10:08,501
I bet you do.

755
01:10:13,178 --> 01:10:14,160
I was afraid...

756
01:10:14,426 --> 01:10:18,103
Are you going to bawl all over it,
or are you gonna open it?

757
01:10:20,251 --> 01:10:23,961
I was gonna wait till tomorrow
to tell you all this, but what the heck?

758
01:10:24,795 --> 01:10:28,024
With this bonus check,
I'm putting in a swimming pool.

759
01:10:32,187 --> 01:10:34,327
That's it. That's the big one!

760
01:10:36,668 --> 01:10:37,683
Open it!

761
01:10:40,316 --> 01:10:43,611
I'm sorry if I've been
a little short with everyone lately.

762
01:10:44,156 --> 01:10:45,879
I've been waiting for this bonus.

763
01:10:46,140 --> 01:10:48,181
To make sure the pool goes in
when the ground thaws...

764
01:10:48,253 --> 01:10:50,162
...I had to lay out the money in advance.

765
01:10:50,237 --> 01:10:54,231
Until this arrived, I didn't have enough
to cover the check.

766
01:10:54,557 --> 01:10:56,662
Tear the sucker open, Dad.

767
01:10:58,333 --> 01:10:59,129
Drum roll.

768
01:11:07,678 --> 01:11:11,606
If there's enough left,
I'll fly you all down to help us dedicate it.

769
01:11:15,550 --> 01:11:17,044
I can't swim, Clark.

770
01:11:18,367 --> 01:11:19,610
I know that, Eddie.

771
01:11:33,983 --> 01:11:35,129
What's wrong?

772
01:11:38,336 --> 01:11:40,572
It's bigger than you expected?

773
01:11:44,127 --> 01:11:45,054
Smaller?

774
01:11:47,776 --> 01:11:48,889
What is it?

775
01:11:50,625 --> 01:11:54,269
A one-year membership
in the Jelly-of-the-Month Club.

776
01:11:55,392 --> 01:11:59,221
That's the gift that keeps on giving
the whole year.

777
01:12:00,896 --> 01:12:02,304
That it is, Edward.

778
01:12:03,233 --> 01:12:04,345
That it is, indeed.

779
01:12:05,217 --> 01:12:06,330
I'm sorry.

780
01:12:08,417 --> 01:12:13,054
If this isn't the biggest bag-over-the-head
punch in the face I ever got! Goddamn it!

781
01:12:14,049 --> 01:12:14,812
Son.

782
01:12:27,714 --> 01:12:29,307
It's good.

783
01:12:37,890 --> 01:12:41,338
If any of you are looking
for any last-minute gift ideas for me...

784
01:12:41,411 --> 01:12:42,655
...I have one.

785
01:12:43,394 --> 01:12:46,012
I'd like Frank Shirley,
my boss, right here, tonight.

786
01:12:46,979 --> 01:12:51,136
Brought from his happy holiday slumber
on Melody Lane with all the rich people.

787
01:12:51,300 --> 01:12:53,209
I want him brought right here...

788
01:12:53,540 --> 01:12:57,696
...with a big ribbon on his head and
I want to look him straight in the eye...

789
01:12:57,955 --> 01:13:01,304
...and I want to tell him
what a cheap, lying, no good, rotten...

790
01:13:01,379 --> 01:13:04,446
...low-life, snake-licking, dirt-eating,
inbred, overstuffed...

791
01:13:04,580 --> 01:13:08,923
...ignorant, bloodsucking,
brainless, dickless, hopeless...

792
01:13:09,380 --> 01:13:12,893
...heartless, fat-assed, bug-eyed,
stiff-legged, spotty-lipped...

793
01:13:13,060 --> 01:13:15,929
...worm-headed sack of monkey shit he is!

794
01:13:16,260 --> 01:13:17,538
Hallelujah!

795
01:13:17,957 --> 01:13:20,258
Holy shit! Where's the Tylenol?

796
01:13:33,318 --> 01:13:35,172
He has that crazy look in his eye.

797
01:13:35,238 --> 01:13:37,474
I told you we should have gone to Hawaii.

798
01:13:37,798 --> 01:13:40,253
Turn that thing off and get in the house!

799
01:13:40,998 --> 01:13:42,590
I'll talk to him, Mom.

800
01:13:46,022 --> 01:13:47,332
You know, Dad...

801
01:13:47,462 --> 01:13:48,989
...l've been thinking.

802
01:13:50,502 --> 01:13:51,877
Good talk.

803
01:13:57,478 --> 01:14:00,326
Aren't you a teeny bit sorry
we didn't get a Christmas tree?

804
01:14:00,423 --> 01:14:03,457
Even though they're dirty and messy
and corny and clichd?

805
01:14:03,943 --> 01:14:06,977
Where are you going to find a tree
at this hour on Christmas Eve?

806
01:14:25,512 --> 01:14:26,373
What's the matter?

807
01:14:28,585 --> 01:14:29,795
Was that really necessary?

808
01:14:32,201 --> 01:14:33,411
We needed a tree.

809
01:14:33,481 --> 01:14:35,074
May I remind you that...

810
01:14:35,241 --> 01:14:38,275
That this was all my idea?
No, no. I'm well aware of that.

811
01:14:38,985 --> 01:14:42,182
Could you just keep it in mind
the next time you go berserk?

812
01:14:42,505 --> 01:14:45,538
I didn't go berserk.
I simply solved a problem.

813
01:14:47,722 --> 01:14:49,216
We needed a coffin.

814
01:14:50,506 --> 01:14:53,954
A tree. There are no lots open
on Christmas Eve.

815
01:14:54,346 --> 01:14:58,121
Louis burned down my tree
so I replaced it as best I could. Voil...

816
01:14:58,666 --> 01:14:59,843
Are you okay?

817
01:14:59,946 --> 01:15:01,474
I'm fine, honey.

818
01:15:25,068 --> 01:15:26,661
I fixed the newel post.

819
01:15:48,781 --> 01:15:50,122
What's that sound?

820
01:16:11,150 --> 01:16:12,427
Do you hear it?

821
01:16:13,390 --> 01:16:15,725
It's a funny, squeaking sound.

822
01:16:16,431 --> 01:16:20,741
You couldn't hear a dump truck
driving through a nitroglycerin plant.

823
01:16:22,191 --> 01:16:23,434
I hear it, too.

824
01:16:32,079 --> 01:16:33,061
I don't hear it anymore.

825
01:16:38,192 --> 01:16:39,468
Squirrel!

826
01:16:46,929 --> 01:16:48,751
What was it? Oh, my God!

827
01:16:54,832 --> 01:16:56,109
Quiet! Shut up!

828
01:17:09,233 --> 01:17:10,509
Mom, don't move.

829
01:17:12,913 --> 01:17:14,954
We can't let it out of the living room.

830
01:17:16,082 --> 01:17:18,832
Where's Eddie?
He usually eats these goddamn things.

831
01:17:19,154 --> 01:17:22,602
Not recently, Clark. He read that squirrels
were high in cholesterol.

832
01:17:23,794 --> 01:17:25,004
Thank you, Catherine.

833
01:17:26,449 --> 01:17:27,627
I'll try and trap it.

834
01:17:27,794 --> 01:17:28,809
Russ!

835
01:17:29,042 --> 01:17:30,025
We're here, Dad.

836
01:17:30,642 --> 01:17:31,624
There you are.

837
01:17:32,755 --> 01:17:34,097
Go get the hammer.

838
01:17:34,355 --> 01:17:36,210
What do you need a hammer for?

839
01:17:36,435 --> 01:17:40,047
I'll catch it in the coat
and smack it with the hammer.

840
01:17:47,156 --> 01:17:48,683
I'm going in with him.

841
01:17:52,275 --> 01:17:53,388
Nora?

842
01:17:56,852 --> 01:17:57,800
Is it gone?

843
01:17:57,876 --> 01:18:00,266
It probably got scared
and ran back into the tree.

844
01:18:01,012 --> 01:18:02,670
Squirrel!

845
01:18:39,830 --> 01:18:43,792
You just march right over there
and slug that creep in the face.

846
01:18:43,959 --> 01:18:45,421
I can't just attack someone.

847
01:18:45,495 --> 01:18:49,553
All right, then. If you're not man enough
to put an end to this shit, then I am.

848
01:19:10,455 --> 01:19:11,121
Gone.

849
01:19:16,441 --> 01:19:17,968
Oh, my God.

850
01:19:21,016 --> 01:19:22,445
What happened to you?

851
01:19:34,842 --> 01:19:37,395
Where do you think you're going?
Nobody's leaving.

852
01:19:37,722 --> 01:19:40,471
Nobody walks out
on this old-fashioned family Christmas.

853
01:19:40,537 --> 01:19:42,839
No, we're all in this together.

854
01:19:43,162 --> 01:19:46,032
This is a full-blown,
four-alarm holiday emergency.

855
01:19:46,298 --> 01:19:49,495
We're going to press on
and have the happiest Christmas...

856
01:19:49,658 --> 01:19:52,375
...since Bing Crosby tap-danced
with Danny fucking Kaye.

857
01:19:52,442 --> 01:19:55,344
And when Santa squeezes
his fat, white ass down the chimney...

858
01:19:55,418 --> 01:19:59,248
...he's gonna find the jolliest bunch
of assholes this side of the nuthouse.

859
01:19:59,450 --> 01:20:00,628
You're goofy.

860
01:20:00,923 --> 01:20:02,516
Don't piss me off, Art.

861
01:20:03,643 --> 01:20:06,611
- It's over.
- Not according to Santa's watch, it isn't.

862
01:20:06,683 --> 01:20:07,893
Stay out of this, Dad.

863
01:20:07,963 --> 01:20:10,930
Clark, I think it's best
if everyone just goes home.

864
01:20:11,259 --> 01:20:12,787
Before things get worse.

865
01:20:12,860 --> 01:20:15,729
Worse?! How could they get any worse?

866
01:20:15,964 --> 01:20:19,793
Look around you, Ellen.
We're at the threshold of hell!

867
01:20:37,085 --> 01:20:38,033
Son.

868
01:20:39,805 --> 01:20:42,041
I love you. We all love you.

869
01:20:42,364 --> 01:20:45,714
But this is a terrible night.
Nothing's gone right. It's a disaster.

870
01:20:46,461 --> 01:20:49,178
But losing your temper
only makes things worse.

871
01:20:49,405 --> 01:20:51,958
You're too good a father to act like this.

872
01:20:53,885 --> 01:20:58,359
In years to come, you'll want your family
to remember all the love you gave us...

873
01:20:58,622 --> 01:21:01,556
...and how hard you tried
to make the perfect Christmas.

874
01:21:02,142 --> 01:21:03,669
You just cocked it up.

875
01:21:06,526 --> 01:21:08,763
It's okay. It happens.

876
01:21:10,782 --> 01:21:13,020
All our holidays were always such a mess.

877
01:21:15,007 --> 01:21:16,730
How did you get through it?

878
01:21:17,567 --> 01:21:19,477
I had a lot of help from Jack Daniels.

879
01:21:28,768 --> 01:21:30,044
I love you.

880
01:21:34,464 --> 01:21:36,536
Will you recite
"The Night Before Christmas"?

881
01:21:36,608 --> 01:21:38,844
No. It's your house.

882
01:21:39,103 --> 01:21:40,598
It's your Christmas.

883
01:21:41,727 --> 01:21:43,255
I'm retiring.

884
01:21:44,577 --> 01:21:47,326
"The children were nestled
All snug in their beds

885
01:21:47,648 --> 01:21:50,518
"While visions of sugarplums
Danced in their heads

886
01:21:51,105 --> 01:21:52,534
"And Mama in her kerchief

887
01:21:52,608 --> 01:21:56,438
"And I in my cap, just settled our brains
For a long winter's nap

888
01:21:56,705 --> 01:22:00,054
"When out on the lawn
There arose such a clatter

889
01:22:00,162 --> 01:22:02,300
"I sprang from my bed
To see what was the matter

890
01:22:02,370 --> 01:22:04,409
"Away to the window I flew like a flash

891
01:22:04,577 --> 01:22:06,814
"Tore open the shutters
and threw up the sash

892
01:22:07,009 --> 01:22:08,919
"The moon on the breast of
the new-fallen snow

893
01:22:08,994 --> 01:22:11,415
"Gave a luster of midday to objects below

894
01:22:11,585 --> 01:22:13,822
"When what to my wondering eyes
should appear

895
01:22:13,922 --> 01:22:15,548
"But a miniature sleigh..."

896
01:22:17,218 --> 01:22:18,047
...and Eddie.

897
01:22:18,370 --> 01:22:20,923
And a man in his pajamas
with a dog chain...

898
01:22:21,090 --> 01:22:23,424
...tied to his wrists and ankles.
What the...?

899
01:22:25,731 --> 01:22:26,844
Stay here.

900
01:22:32,931 --> 01:22:34,906
Merry Christmas, Clark.

901
01:22:36,131 --> 01:22:38,848
You about ready to do some kissin'?

902
01:22:40,451 --> 01:22:43,102
Officer, it seems
my husband has been abducted.

903
01:22:43,332 --> 01:22:46,845
The man was wearing a blue leisure suit...

904
01:22:48,292 --> 01:22:53,027
...and the plates were from Kansas.
He was a huge, beastly, bulging man.

905
01:22:53,348 --> 01:22:55,584
I have never been treated
like this in my life.

906
01:22:55,812 --> 01:22:58,049
I'm sorry.
This is our family's first kidnapping.

907
01:22:59,044 --> 01:23:00,222
You're fired.

908
01:23:00,612 --> 01:23:02,368
Where's the phone? I'm calling the police.

909
01:23:02,437 --> 01:23:04,346
Just hold your wad there, fella.

910
01:23:04,613 --> 01:23:08,289
Clark had nothin' to do with this.
This here was my idea.

911
01:23:08,548 --> 01:23:11,965
All right. He's still fired
and you are going to jail.

912
01:23:13,734 --> 01:23:15,261
It was my fault.

913
01:23:16,294 --> 01:23:20,287
I lost my temper when I got my bonus
and I said a few things I shouldn't have.

914
01:23:20,454 --> 01:23:24,927
Bonus? How did you get a bonus?
I cut out bonuses this year.

915
01:23:26,055 --> 01:23:27,516
Thanks for telling us.

916
01:23:27,590 --> 01:23:30,786
I was expecting a check.
Instead I got enrolled in a jelly club.

917
01:23:31,334 --> 01:23:35,163
In 17 years with the company, I've gotten
a bonus every year, but this one.

918
01:23:35,494 --> 01:23:37,349
You don't want to give bonuses, fine!

919
01:23:37,510 --> 01:23:39,779
When people count on them
as part of their salary...

920
01:23:40,007 --> 01:23:41,666
What you did just plain...

921
01:23:41,799 --> 01:23:42,814
Sucks.

922
01:23:44,615 --> 01:23:45,891
Thank you, Russ.

923
01:23:49,415 --> 01:23:52,132
My cousin-in-law,
whose heart is bigger than his brain...

924
01:23:52,391 --> 01:23:53,885
I appreciate that.

925
01:23:55,175 --> 01:23:58,143
...is innocent. I'll be more than happy
to take the rap on this...

926
01:23:58,536 --> 01:24:02,365
...on behalf of myself and every other
employee you rear-ended this Christmas.

927
01:24:23,593 --> 01:24:26,376
Sometimes things look good
on paper, but...

928
01:24:26,634 --> 01:24:30,376
...lose their luster when you see
how it affects real folks.

929
01:24:31,338 --> 01:24:33,727
A healthy bottom line
doesn't mean much if...

930
01:24:33,802 --> 01:24:36,769
...to get it, you have to hurt
the ones you depend on.

931
01:24:38,858 --> 01:24:43,168
It's people that make the difference.
Little people, like you.

932
01:24:45,674 --> 01:24:47,584
So, Carl...

933
01:24:49,258 --> 01:24:51,200
...whatever you got last year...

934
01:24:51,818 --> 01:24:54,054
...add 20 percent.

935
01:25:44,942 --> 01:25:46,851
Go away, Todd.

936
01:25:47,949 --> 01:25:52,292
If you want to come in, you are gonna
have to break down the goddamn door!

937
01:26:03,022 --> 01:26:06,056
Merry Christmas to all
and to all a good night!

938
01:26:17,104 --> 01:26:18,216
Freeze!

939
01:26:20,303 --> 01:26:22,059
Not you! Them!

940
01:26:31,504 --> 01:26:32,781
This way, please.

941
01:26:35,664 --> 01:26:37,518
I think you've made a terrible mistake.

942
01:26:37,840 --> 01:26:39,270
I told you to freeze, mister.

943
01:26:39,505 --> 01:26:40,682
May we blink?

944
01:26:47,185 --> 01:26:50,054
- Thank God you're all right.
- I'm fine. I'm just fine.

945
01:26:50,385 --> 01:26:52,294
There was a big
misunderstanding tonight.

946
01:26:52,817 --> 01:26:57,073
Excuse me. Would you and Mrs. Shirley
like to step outside so we can finish here?

947
01:26:58,066 --> 01:27:00,553
- Don't bother. I'm not pressing charges.
- What?

948
01:27:01,585 --> 01:27:02,829
It was a mistake.

949
01:27:02,897 --> 01:27:05,515
Mistake? Honey, you were kidnapped.

950
01:27:05,842 --> 01:27:07,816
I did something I shouldn't have...

951
01:27:07,986 --> 01:27:12,395
...and these people called me on it.
This is Clark Griswold and his family.

952
01:27:12,787 --> 01:27:14,216
Welcome to our home.

953
01:27:15,507 --> 01:27:16,848
What's left of it.

954
01:27:16,946 --> 01:27:18,255
Release B Squad.

955
01:27:18,547 --> 01:27:19,921
What's going on here?

956
01:27:20,146 --> 01:27:24,304
Remember how I was toying with the
notion of suspending Christmas bonuses?

957
01:27:24,947 --> 01:27:26,224
You didn't.

958
01:27:26,483 --> 01:27:29,679
Of all the cheap,
lousy ways to save a buck!

959
01:27:29,907 --> 01:27:31,282
That's pretty low, mister.

960
01:27:31,827 --> 01:27:33,354
If I had a rubber hose...

961
01:27:33,427 --> 01:27:35,664
I changed my mind.
I'm reinstating all the bonuses.

962
01:27:41,044 --> 01:27:42,637
Look!

963
01:27:44,948 --> 01:27:46,060
Look!

964
01:27:52,468 --> 01:27:54,062
It's Santy Claus.

965
01:27:57,749 --> 01:27:59,822
Uncle Clark, it's Santy Claus.

966
01:28:01,269 --> 01:28:02,894
It's the Christmas star.

967
01:28:03,349 --> 01:28:05,105
And that's all that matters tonight.

968
01:28:06,708 --> 01:28:10,386
Not bonuses or gifts or turkeys or trees.

969
01:28:10,966 --> 01:28:12,242
See, kids...

970
01:28:13,206 --> 01:28:15,508
It means something different
to everybody.

971
01:28:17,685 --> 01:28:19,409
Now I know what it means to me.

972
01:28:21,269 --> 01:28:23,507
That ain't the frigging Christmas star.

973
01:28:23,671 --> 01:28:26,704
It's the light
on the sewage treatment plant.

974
01:28:26,966 --> 01:28:28,242
Sewer gas.

975
01:28:30,166 --> 01:28:31,475
Don't drop that!

976
01:28:41,112 --> 01:28:43,501
"And the rocket's red glare

977
01:28:44,471 --> 01:28:47,505
"The bombs bursting in air

978
01:28:48,247 --> 01:28:50,386
"Gave proof through the night

979
01:28:51,447 --> 01:28:54,797
"That our flag was still there

980
01:28:55,832 --> 01:28:57,904
"Oh, say does that

981
01:28:57,976 --> 01:29:02,384
"Star-spangled banner yet wave

982
01:29:04,632 --> 01:29:07,501
"O'er the land of the free

983
01:29:10,073 --> 01:29:13,902
"And the home of the brave?"

984
01:29:18,233 --> 01:29:19,760
Play ball!

985
01:29:27,513 --> 01:29:29,423
Merry Christmas, Sparky.

986
01:29:30,393 --> 01:29:31,954
Merry Christmas, honey.

987
01:29:59,867 --> 01:30:00,947
I did it.